The fifth William Davenport inherited Bramall in 1585 from his father of the same name, and lived there with his wife Dorothy for over 50 years.
The first marriage in Bramall's chapel was recorded in 1599, between William (aged 15) - the eldest son of the fifth William and Dorothy - and Frances Wilbraham (aged 11).
